edu.uga.dawgtrades.model

Interface Category

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Persistable

    public interface Category
extends Persistable
    This interface represents a Category. It has a collection of methods to read/write Category's attributes. Category (optionally) participates in an association with another Category (parent), where the class at the other end has a multiplicity of 1. Getters/setters for the identifiers of the one side objects are included, as well. It also extends the Persistable interface, since objects of this class will be stored in the persistent data store.
